3. Pointers as Function Arguments - Call by Reference

1.Write a function to swap two integers using call by reference.
2.Implement a program to find the maximum and minimum elements in an array using pointers as function arguments.
3.Write a program to reverse a string using call by reference.
4.Implement a function that changes the value of an integer using call by reference.
5.Create a program to sort an array using a pointer to the array passed as a function argument.
6.Write a program to find the sum of two numbers using call by reference.
7.Implement a program to rotate an array using call by reference.
8.Create a function to modify the elements of a 2D array using call by reference.
9.Write a program to perform matrix multiplication using call by reference.
10.Implement a program to swap the contents of two arrays using call by reference.
